# Parsar docker build context filter.
#
# We default to "deny most" with explicit allow-lines, so a stray
# secret file (~/.env, *.pem, etc.) the operator drops in the repo
# does NOT silently flow into the build context — and from there
# into intermediate layers an attacker who pulls the image could
# extract.
#
# Each pattern below is anchored to the repo root.

# Repo runtime / state directories that must never enter the image.
.mavis/
.harness/
.opencode/
.parsar/
.worktrees/
.fork-point
deliverable.md

# Local dev databases, sockets, postgres data volumes.
docker/postgres/data/
*.sock

# Build outputs from host runs of `make` / `pnpm build` / `go build`.
# The image rebuilds these from source inside the multi-stage build,
# so shipping the host versions would only bloat the context and
# risk cross-platform binary mismatches.
**/dist/
**/build/
**/coverage/
**/node_modules/
server/bin/
out/

# Git metadata — adds size and triggers cache invalidations on
# unrelated commits. The image does not need git history at runtime.
.git/
.gitignore
.gitattributes

# Editor / IDE droppings.
.DS_Store
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp

# Local env / secret files. We list known-secret file names
# explicitly so a typo'd suffix (e.g. .env.production-prod-real-final)
# doesn't slip through a permissive pattern — and so legitimate
# source files like apps/web/src/lib/api-secrets.ts (the Vault HTTP
# client) are NOT swept up.
#
# DO NOT add bare wildcards like `**/secret*` or `**/*-secret*` here:
# they match too widely (api-secrets.ts, secret-handling docs, etc.)
# and break the web build.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
**/*.pem
**/*.key
**/credentials.json
**/.npmrc
**/id_rsa
**/id_ed25519
**/.aws/credentials

# Test artefacts / playground that aren't needed in the image.
tests/.evidence/
tests/.playwright-report/
tests/playwright-report/
tests/playwright/.cache/

# Test files never enter the image. Excludes Go *_test.go and web
# *.test.ts/.tsx plus any testdata directories, with the runtime
# crypto wire fixture re-allowed because parsar-server reads it from
# disk at runtime.
**/*_test.go
**/*.test.ts
**/*.test.tsx
**/testdata/**
!internal/runtimecrypto/testdata/**

# Lockfile we DO want: pnpm-lock.yaml stays in the context so the
# web builder can `pnpm install --frozen-lockfile`. (Don't add it to
# this ignore list.)

# CI scratch / coverage from local runs.
*.log
*.lock-info
